    "name": "Routes",
    "description": "StartFragment\n\nCO2 Signal uses API keys to allow access to the API. You can get an API key [here](http://www.co2signal.com/).\n\nCO2 Signal expects the API key to be included as a header in all requests to the server:\n\n`auth-token: myapitoken`\n\nEndFragment",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "1487263"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Get latest by country code",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://api.co2signal.com/v1/latest?countryCode={{CountryCode}}",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": [
            "api",
            "co2signal",
            "com"
          ],
          "path": [
            "v1",
            "latest"
          ],
          "query": [
            {
              "key": "countryCode",
              "value": "{{CountryCode}}",
              "description": "two-letter iso country code"
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "StartFragment\n\nThis endpoint retrieves the last known state of a country. It is also possible to get data for a specific zone, in case the country is divided by zones seen on app.electricitymap.org.\n\nSee [http://api.electricitymap.org/v3/zones](http://api.electricitymap.org/v3/zones) for list of available zones.\n\nEndFragme"
      },
